I have created the three files to redesign the Invoicer UI using the context from `STACK.md`, `research-brief.md`, and `functional-spec.md`.

1. **`design-brief.md`**: Contains the shared design system. It establishes a premium brand identity inspired by FreshBooks, with an intuitive layout and clear color tokens (primary indigo, success emerald, danger red). 
2. **`landing-prototype.html`**: A complete marketing website mockup using the design tokens. It features a sticky navigation, hero section with call-to-actions, feature grid highlighting the core functionalities, and a transparent pricing section leading with the "Free Forever" tier.
3. **`app-prototype.html`**: A comprehensive in-app UI mockup simulating a single-page application. It uses a lightweight vanilla JavaScript script to toggle between multiple screens (Authentication, Dashboard, Invoices list, Invoice detail/form, Clients list/form, Catalog, and Settings). It integrates the same typography, layout spacing, and CSS variables established in the design brief.

All prototypes use plain HTML, CSS, and minimal JS as requested, without any external asset dependencies (all icons are inline SVGs).
